   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Urban Tilth&apos;s Urban Agriculture Institute</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Our Urban Agriculture Institute is a year-round, student-driven &quot;farm, classroom, and community&quot; program that changes the way students think about our food system, and our world. The program engages low-income youth at Richmond High School in a school-year accredited course in urban agriculture and food systems; provides hands-on farming in our 8,000 square foot farm at the school; employs them in our 100-hour Summer Youth Apprenticeship; and takes them on field trips to rural sustainable farms.</narrative>
  </description>
